metadata.name: 01. morph stripes (revised) #7
metadata.description:
A set of procedurally animated points that define an isosurface is then run through the marching cubes algorithm to generate a polygonal mesh. The shading is a cheap implementation of the spherical environment mapping (matcap) algorithm, using a striped black and white texture.

The result is a hypnotic metaball animation with an op-art vibe.

This is probably one of the first implementations of GPGPU marching cubes that were ever done in WebGL, courtesy of Hector Arellano.

Created in Apr 2014, minted in Nov 2021
by Felix Martinez - @sirokos

Note: Revised version using fxrand(). If you minted the previous iteration and I didn't reach out to you, please get in touch.

metadata.name: The Moth Experiment #12
metadata.description:
The Moth Experiment is a series of hand drawn moths that have been generated using code to create 77 variations.

Insects have always evoked awe. The underrated beauty of moths with their alluring and intriguing patterns and textures drew me to them. This compelled me to explore these wonderful creatures in my own style.

Each of these pieces have rarities attached to them namely;
Background
Antlers
Body
Forewings
Hindwings

This is the 1st season of The Moth Experiment and will consist of 77, 1/1 variations. 

In the previous drop there were 41 minted, hence in this drop, I am minting 36 editions.
 Are you going to be the first ones to fly towards this flame?

metadata.name: intentions 01 #45
metadata.description:
A 3D map of an imaginary cavern is created with Perlin noise; this is sliced in to an arbitrary stack, and each slice is rendered as a dot field. This is, in turn, displayed on the screen as a rotating isometric cube. Along the bottom, one can see the total number of slices, and the gradient created by the two colors used.

Traits: 

Color 1 & Color 2: each chosen from a single pool of 10. Each color is equally likely, so the least likely result is two of the same color. 

Resolution: This is the resolution of the dot field, and describes the complexity. Three possible results, with 1 being the least likely.

Slices: The number of slices in the stack, with 5 being the least likely. 

Created in p5.js

metadata.name: HallSlider L8P #2
metadata.description:
A looping pattern is generated from the fxhash which determines a randomly sampled phase factor in the range 0<phase<π.

**click/touch** the canvas along the vertical direction to increase/decrease the motion velocity, and near the center to stop the motion.
